        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-3 mt-8">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-4 mb-8"><div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4"><h3 class="text-sm font-bold mb-2">How much does fire alarm installation cost for a Dallas restaurant?</h3><p class="text-sm text-gray-600">A restaurant in Dallas typically costs $1,500–$6,000 for fire alarm installation depending on size. This includes the fire alarm control panel, smoke and heat detectors, pull stations, horn/strobe notification devices, and connection to central station monitoring. Larger restaurant spaces or those in multi-tenant buildings may cost more due to integration requirements.</p></div><div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4"><h3 class="text-sm font-bold mb-2">What type of fire alarm system does Dallas require?</h3><p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Dallas generally requires addressable fire alarm systems for buildings above a certain size or occupancy threshold. Addressable systems allow individual device identification — more expensive than conventional systems but required for most commercial occupancies. Verify specific requirements with Dallas Fire-Rescue based on your building's occupancy type, size, and sprinkler status.</p></div><div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4"><h3 class="text-sm font-bold mb-2">Do I need a permit for fire alarm installation in Dallas?</h3><p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Yes. Dallas Fire-Rescue requires permits for fire alarm system installation and significant modifications. Permit fees typically run $100–$500+ based on system valuation. A Dallas Fire-Rescue inspection is required before the system is placed in service. Use a licensed Texas fire alarm contractor — all fire alarm work in Texas must be performed by contractors licensed under the Texas State Fire Marshal's Office.</p></div><div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4"><h3 class="text-sm font-bold mb-2">How much does fire alarm annual testing cost in Dallas?</h3><p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Annual fire alarm testing in the Dallas metro area typically costs $350–$1,200 for commercial systems, depending on size and complexity. High-rise buildings with voice evacuation, elevator recall, and smoke management integration will be on the higher end. Use a TDI-licensed fire alarm contractor for annual testing.</p></div></div>
